result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both Cause Injury/Operate While und.Influence (1st) (PAC<0.15) and Cause Injury while Operating with PAC (1st) (PAC<0.15). The defendant was found guilty of Cause Injury/Operate While und.Influence (1st) (PAC<0.15) and the other charge, Cause Injury while Operating with PAC (1st) (PAC<0.15) was dismissed by the court.

  • James E Bartlett was found guilty of Battery, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • James E Bartlett was found guilty of Cause Injury/Operate While und.Influence (1st) (PAC<0.15), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(2)(a)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attonrey Bucher makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

6 MONTHS HUBER (CREDIT - 3 days)

____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;

prescribed.
